If set to @{fg fill}NO@{fg text}, he isn't interested anyway in this conference and has simply
turned it off. Do not mischange this with SysOp defined conference access,
which is not set up here. @{b}UserCnfXS@{ub} is part of the user settings.
If you want to deny any conference access for the user, go back to the main
menu and then switch to the @{"Conference Access" link InUsEd_TabConfAccess} sub editor using the TAB hotkey.

