@node "Goodies" "Doors as Goodies"

                                @{b}Doors as Goodies
                               ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

   The FAME release will have additional goodies in form of additional doors
                  and tools which are able to run under FAME.

          These Doors and Tools are written by the @{"FAME Support Team" link "AboutSupportTeam"}.

 All these Doors and Tools are public releases and are unregistered versions.

  If you want to register them you will get full support and also beta tester
             status for all the tools and doors they have written.
      Means you do not pay for one tool, you pay for all tools written by
          one coder till today and all new Tools and Doors in future.

      Your advantage is that you will have access to all tools and doors,
           beta status, full support, backdoor and virus free tools.

         Also most goodies included in the FAME release archive are not
      in the latest versions and are not in the complete functionality the
                              registered ones are.


                         @{b}How to register? Try this one:@{ub}

                               @{"FAME Support Team" link "AboutSupportTeam"}


      You will find the goodies in the FAME archive you will have received
       on registering the first time or in the FAME demo version archive
                               in the directory:

                                    Goodies

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "Miscellaneous" "Miscellaneous things"

                              @{b}Miscellaneous things
                             ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

@{b}@{u}Text view break/clearscreen@{ub}@{uu}

 - You can press on every text viewing in FAME following Ctrl keys:

   - Ctrl-C: To break the view.
   - Ctrl-L: To do a clear screen.

   Note that it can happen that the usage of the Ctrl keys takes no effect,
   this depends on the fact that the serial input buffer of your terminal
   will be filled up if your screen begins to scroll. Scrolling slows
   the text output much down. Because of this there is too much text
   available often as much as the mail is long and if you press a Ctrl
   key the mail may be viewed completely at the BBS, but not at the
   Terminal.


@{b}@{u}Re-creation of UserConf data files@{ub}@{uu}

 - If something damages your UserCnf.data data files (the data files located
   in every of your conferences) you can let the @{"Server" link "InternModules"} re-create them.

   To do this you must shutdown FAME completely including the @{"Server" link "InternModules"}.
   Next is to rename your user.data and user.keys files.
   Now start the @{"Server" link "InternModules"}.

   The @{"Server" link "InternModules"} will pop up a requester to inform you that you have no user data
   files, but User Conf data files.
   You now can let the @{"Server" link "InternModules"} delete them if you select the left button.
   You have to do this for every conference you have, because the requester
   will pop up for every single conference in which such a User Conf data file
   exists.

   If no more requesters appear the @{"Server" link "InternModules"} will open it's main window.
   Now your are in the same state as if you had installed FAME the very first
   time to your system. If you now log on as a newuser FAME will create all
   user data files new, but that isn't exactly what we want.

   That's the reason why you should do nothing just quit the @{"Server" link "InternModules"} again.

   Now it's time to re-rename your original user.data and user.keys files
   back.

   If you now start the @{"Server" link "InternModules"} again it will automaticly create all User Conf
   data files (UserCnf.data) into your conferences.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "FAMESwitchWindow" "FAMESwitchWindow"

                                @{b}FAMESwitchWindow
                               ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

FAMESwitchWindow is an external AmigaDOS program. It may be used to shuffle
Window activating on FAME Node screens. This may be useful if you often
have several windows opened on FAME Node screens, e.g. compiler Shell,
text editor and so on. After Compiling a program, you may wish to have the
Node's Main window activated, for example.
FAMESwitchWindow may be installed as a DOS command at your favourite text
editor, or as a HotKey within the FKey commodity.


@{b}@{u}FAMESwitchWindow does the following things:@{ub}@{uu}

1. Checks if the currently active window is placed on a FAME Node screen.
   If not, the program exits.

2. Activates the next Window on the same screen. If there is only one window,
   nothing happens. Due to technical reasons, the Node close gadget is defined
   as a window. This window is always skipped and won't ever be activated
   by FAMESwitchWindow.

3. ReturnCode is always set to NULL, because other codes would cause the FKey
   commodity to open an output window..


                               @{b}FKey installation:
                              ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

To install FAMESwitchWindow as a system HotKey, just do the following steps:

1. Start the @{b}FKey@{ub} commodity (found on your WorkBench disks), or pop-up it's
   interface from within the @{b}Exchange@{ub} commodity.

2. Select @{fg fill}New Key@{fg text} (gadget placed bottom-left)

3. Enter your new HotKey definition (For Example: @{fg fill}alt .@{fg text}).

4. Set the @{b}Command@{ub} cycle gadget to @{fg fill}Run Program@{fg text}.

5. Enter @{fg fill}FAME:Modules/ExternModules/FAMESwitchWindow@{fg text} as @{b}Command Parameters@{ub}.

6. Hit @{fg fill}ramiga@{fg text}-@{fg fill}s@{fg text} to save all defined keys.

7. Hit @{fg fill}ramiga@{fg text}-@{fg fill}h@{fg text} to hide the FKey commodity interface.

8. Activate a window on a FAME Node screen (screen must have at least one
   additional window to see any effects) and hit @{fg fill}alt@{fg text}-@{fg fill}.@{fg text} several times.

@endnode

