                    How to contact @{" David Wettig " link "DavidWettig"}


        - @{"MainPart" link "InternModules"}       : - GUI.
                           - User handling.
                           - Editor lists and MsgBase.
                           - Asynchronous Window handling.
                           - Internal UserEditor.
                           - Serial code.
                           - XPR implementation.
                           - MCI-Interpreter.
                           - Door systems.
                           - Arexx implementation.
                           - LogFile system.
                           - List developing.
                           - Script handling.
                           - Node to Node communications.
                           - Capture system.
                           - FiFo implementation.
                           - External Filechecker implementation.
                           - ZippySearch.
                           - Internal Doors (WHO/FRONTEND/OLM/...).
                           - Many different other things.

        - @{"Server" link "InternModules"}         : - GUI.
                           - Complete functions.
                           - Node handling.
                           - MessagePort system.
                           - FAMESemaphore and depending list.
                           - Serverlists.

        - @{"SystemEditor" link "InternModules"}   : - GUI.
                           - Complete functions.

        - FAMEFileChecker: - Complete functions.

        - FAMEHydra      : - GUI.
                           - Complete functions.

        - Miscellaneous  : - Developing of the FAME Door Interfaces (FIM)
                             and all additional objectcodes including
                             example sources in C for door coding,
                             containing support versions and
                             freely available versions.
                           - Definition of many different standards.

        - Documentation  : - Different documentations, AmigaGuide.

