@REM==============================================================================

@node "Registration" "Registration"

                              @{b}How to register FAME
                             ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

                        FAME registration fee is 150 DM.

To order your FAME call the FAME main registration site @{" pUNISHMENT iNC. " link "Punishment"}
and log on with your username. Please answer @{b}ALL@{ub} questions, or you
will be kicked out of the BBS!


If you reach the main menu prompt enter @{b}account@{ub} to register yourself
for FAME.

Please write here all the datas you will be asked for.
This will be your SysOp name, your BBS name and your country you want to use
on your BBS, because they will be needed to create your registration number.

The question for your e-mail address musn't be answered, but if you have one
and enter it in the prompt we are able to contact you to send you the latest
informations about FAME.

That's all you have to do in the @{" pUNISHMENT iNC. " link "Punishment"}.

Now send the registration fee of 150 DM to my bank account with your user
name as comment. It's up to you to find out what 150 german marks is in your
currency. You have to send as much money as needed that we receive 150 DM
completely. The best is to exchange to german marks directly at your bank.

Please notice that if you send the money from a bank outside of germany
the bank(s) may take a 20 DM charge for the money transfer. In this case
you have to send 170 DM instead of 150 DM. Please speak with your bank
about this.


           Please send the money to the following bank account:
          ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

                         Bank Name    : Berliner Sparkasse
                         Account Nr   : 1160148798
                         Bank code    : 10050000
                         Account owner: David Wettig


          Some banks are needing more datas (mostly not german ones):
         ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

                           Bank branch: 116
                                Street: Hauptstr. 98/99
                           Postal code: 10827 Berlin, Germany
                            Bank Phone: +49 30 787972-0


                  Your bank may need also my personal address:
                 ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

                                  Name: David
                               Surname: Wettig
                                Street: Feurigstr. 37
                           Postal code: 10827 Berlin, Germany


If you know a better and of course a cheaper way than a banker's order
to send the registration fee to me let us know.

There will be more ways in future like registering and updating via internet
(telnet), but we haven't had the time to set up other ways to register yet.

If we have received your money we will register you to the FAME registration
tool called Registrator.

If you call the next time the @{" pUNISHMENT iNC. " link "Punishment"} and join the
'Final Amiga MailBox Engine' conference you will see that you are registered
if the last text before the menu prompt in this conference is informing you
to enter @{b}REGISTER@{ub} at the menu prompt to get the FAME files.

Now enter @{b}REGISTER@{ub} in the menu prompt to start the Registrator.
You will se a list of coders.

Join the first coder area 'FAME Register' to get all important files
for FAME.

Join also the other coder areas to get more files being a part of FAME you
have paid for.
Those files you will find there are separated, because they are written by
different FAME developers and it's much easier to report bugs and suggestions
to the right persons.

As you will see when calling the Registrator you can do much more than just
downloading files. You may also post bug reports and suggestions in the
Registrator. They can be typed online or can be uploaded as text file.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "DemoVersNotes" "Information about the Demo-Version"

                       @{b}Information about the Demo-Version
                      ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

FAME has been released under the concept of Shareware.

FAME Demo-Version has no longer any limitations except a requester which
appears every time you open a Node screen.

You are allowed to run the unregistered demo version of FAME 30 days long.
After 30 days of usage you have to register or to delete FAME.

I made an exception for door and tool coders which code FAME depending
doors/tools and are *NO* SysOps. FAME door and tool coders are allowed to
use the FAME Demo-Version as long as they are not SysOps and they write
doors/tools for FAME.

FAME Demo-Version has also a very short information delay on every logon
where it informs the caller that you run a Demo-Version.


The requester is not hard to remove, but i've decided to remove the
10 user limit code, because i don't want to have badly cracked FAME
versions spreaded around as it happened lately.

No Software is 100% secure for being cracked and so i think it's better
if people are running working cracks and no fakes and crapy cracked stuff.
Last one will only bring trouble and may destroy someones harddisk or
something similar.

People have to register FAME if they want to get the latest updates of
FAME and there are often updates, nearly every second week or more often.

I also beleave most SysOps like to get the support and they don't want to
install virus infected software so most will register one day.


       Every registration also supports the development of FAME !!!

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "NotImplemented" "Not implemented yet"

                              @{b}Not implemented yet
                             ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

              Sorry, but this option is currently not implemented!

    It was not possible to implement all we want to yet, but because of the
     fact that FAME is well known and everbody cries out for it we have
                        decided to pre-release FAME now.

     If we were to first implement all stuff we want to have in FAME we 
                      would need a complete year for this.

         If you register FAME you *MUST* agree with this, else it wasn't
                         possible to release FAME now.

              Everything will be implemented but it takes time.

      If there is any really important thing which isn't implemented yet
          please note this to the @{"Development Team" link "AboutDevTeam"} and we will try to
                       implement it as soon as possible.

@endnode

